zewell/"], "contributor": ["library of virginia; richmond, va"], "date": "1908-01-09", "dates": ["1908-01-09"], "description": ["TOTEIi REPUBLICAN PUBLISHED EVERY THURSDAY AT TAZEWELL VIRGINIA BY WILLIAM C PENDLETON Editor and Proprietor SUBSCRIPTIONS Republican one year in advance 100 On Time 150 Advertising Rates furnished on ap plication Correspondence solicited The publisher of The Repubucan is not responsible for opinions expressed by Correspondents The Republican is entered at the Postoffice at Tazewell Virginia as secondclass matter THURSDAY JANUARY 9 1908 THE BUSINESS OUTLOOK From present indications the business outlook for 1908 in the United States is good For the past few months then was considerable apprehension among business men this condition being caused by the Wall Street or gamblers panic Conditions however are now rapidly changing Factories mills anl furnaces that had shut down have re sumed and are resuming work and thousands of men that had temporarily been idle are again at work Many opinions have been expressed by public and business men as to what was the cause of the financial strin gency or socalled panic The very dif ficulty that is found in tracing the flurry to its true source is positive proof thai there was no legitimate reason for its origin One of its peculiar features is that it has made but little"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-02-06T12:48:41.082Z", "group": ["ndnp/vi", "library-of-virginia-richmond-va-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn95079154/1908-01-09/ed-1/?sp=2", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:vi:batch_vi_zztop_ver01:data:sn95079154:00175032733:1908010901:0216/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=423&w=331", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:vi:batch_vi_zztop_ver01:data:sn95079154:00175032733:1908010901:0216/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=846&w=663", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/serv